T1  - A Methodology for Determining the Optimal Design of a Free Standing Abortion Clinic
AU  - Gitlow, Howard S.
Y1  - 1976/08/01
PY  - 1976
DA  - 1976/08/01
N1  - doi: 10.1287/mnsc.22.12.1289
DO  - 10.1287/mnsc.22.12.1289
T2  - Management Science
JF  - Management Science
JO  - Management Science
SP  - 1289
EP  - 1298
VL  - 22
IS  - 12
PB  - INFORMS
N2  - In 1970, abortion on demand was legalized in several sections of the United States. Due to increased demand for abortions, free standing abortion clinics came into existence. This paper develops a methodology for determining the optimal design of a free standing abortion clinic, in order to maximize its profits. An example of a clinic which was actually designed employing the methodology is presented, and the results suggest that the methodology is relevant and useful.
AB  - In 1970, abortion on demand was legalized in several sections of the United States. Due to increased demand for abortions, free standing abortion clinics came into existence. This paper develops a methodology for determining the optimal design of a free standing abortion clinic, in order to maximize its profits. An example of a clinic which was actually designed employing the methodology is presented, and the results suggest that the methodology is relevant and useful.
